AudienceMember 20210819QT01 : Was the UK government right to send Royal Navy ships to Jersey amid tensions with French fisherman
the UK government was or was not right to send Royal Navy ships to Jersey amid tensions with French fisherman
John Bercow : it is not constructive
sending the royal navy to a minor fishing dispute is not constructive
John Bercow : it doesn't advance the cause of the arguments that need to be resolved
sending the royal navy to a minor fishing dispute doesn't advance the cause of the arguments that need to be resolved
John Bercow : The truth of the matter is the problem flows from Brexit

Robert Jenrick : I'm pleased the situation has eased
Robert Jenrick : The ships have left the vicinity of Jersey
the ships have left the vicinity of Jersey
Robert Jenrick : We were right to do everything we can to support the people of Jersey and the fishermen

Robert Jenrick : John is right in the sense this issue now needs to be resolved by diplomacy, by the chief minister and the minister of Jersey with the support of the UK government working with counterparts in France and the European Union

John Bercow is right in the sense this issue now needs to be resolved by diplomacy, by the chief minister and the minister of Jersey with the support of the UK government working with counterparts in France and the European Union

Robert Jenrick : It allows Jersey to regulate fishing within its waters and enables them to have a licencing agreement
the agreement between France and Jersey allows Jersey to regulate fishing within its waters and enables them to have a licencing agreement

Robert Jenrick : It sounds like a sensible outcome has been achieved tonight

the French ships have moved away
